<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/1408a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-30T17:00:00-05:00">March 30, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>86. Department has thus far received incomplete information on the nature
                            and extent of the difficulties which have supervened between the French,
                            British and Italians with regard to the final terms of the naval
                            arrangement. Please ascertain as promptly as possible and inform
                            Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>